# Scroll reveal / fade-in defaults

When adding scroll-triggered fade or slide-up animations:

## Do

- Use plain `<section>` (or equivalent) for section wrappers — background, padding, and layout paint immediately.
- Wrap **content inside** the section: headings, cards, list items, form blocks, columns.
- Stagger siblings with small delays (e.g. 60–100ms per item) when it helps readability.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` (hide or skip animation).

## Don't

- Wrap an entire `<section>` in a reveal/fade component (`Reveal as="section"`, Framer Motion on the section root, etc.).
- Fade the full viewport band including section background — it reads as a jarring “black sheet lifting” on dark/light transitions.

## Rationale

Section-level fades fight hard background cuts between bands. Item-level reveals keep the section stable while content enters — clearer hierarchy and less motion sickness on scroll.

## This codebase

Use `Reveal` from `@/components/Reveal` on inner elements only. Portfolio pattern: `MetricStrip`, `Portfolio`, `About`, `Resume`, `Contact`.
